-- Russia Equity Movers: United Co. Rusal, Sberbank, VTB Group
-- B y   A l e x   N i c h o l s o n
-- 2012-03-14T15:09:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-14/russia-equity-movers-united-co-rusal-sberbank-vtb-group.html
The 30-stock Micex Index climbed
for a second day, adding 1.2 percent to 1,631.15 at the close in
Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index was 1.3 percent
stronger at 1,752.02.  The following are among the most active equities in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses  United Co. Rusal (RUALR)  (RUALR RX) dropped 2.5 percent to 225.13
rubles, its weakest close since Jan. 24. Billionaire Chairman
Victor Vekselberg’s March 12 resignation stoked concern a
shareholder dispute will hurt the world’s biggest aluminum
producer.  OAO Sberbank (SBER)  (SBER RX) gained 2.7 percent to 103.26 rubles,
its best rally since Feb. 24. Shares of  Russia ’s biggest lender
advanced as the  Federal Reserve  spurred confidence in the U.S.
banking system and raised its economic assessment.  VTB Group (VTBR) 
(VTBR RX), the country’s second-biggest bank, added 1.9 percent
to 7.328 kopeks, its strongest level in more than a week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Nicholson in Moscow at 
